==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wedgwood ware
<hw>Wedg"wood` ware`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[From the name of the
inventor, Josiah <ets>Wedgwood</ets>, of England.]</ety> <def>A kind of
fine pottery, the most remarkable being what is called
<stype>jasper</stype>, either white, or colored throughout the body, and
capable of being molded into the most delicate forms, so that fine and
minute bas-reliefs like cameos were made of it, fit even for being set
as jewels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wedgy</ent>⟦br⟧
